  "storyboard_markdown": "# Scene Contract: CH001_SC003\n\n## Production Intent\nAlice navigates a lamp-lit corridor of oversized doors to locate a miniature entrance. The sequence relies on precise scale shifts between the character, a glass table with a tiny key, and a small door hidden behind a curtain. Visuals must emphasize the verticality of the hall versus the micro-scale of the discovery.\n\n## Required Cast\n- alice (young human girl, extreme physical instability/scale fluctuation)\n\n## Required Environments\n- hall_of_doors (long, lamp-lit passage with locked doors)\n- glass_table_zone (contains a glass table and tiny golden key)\n- curtain_door_niche (contains a curtain and a small door leading to a garden)\n\n## Continuity Constraints\n- Scale relationship: Alice vs. Doors\n- Scale relationship: Tiny golden key vs. Glass table surface\n- Scale relationship: Alice vs. Small door opening\n- Visual continuity of the garden through the small door\n\n## Beat List\n- BT001: Alice explores the passage\n- BT002: Alice finds the key\n- BT003: Alice discovers the small door\n- BT004: Alice realizes she is too large",
